msgctxt "sn23.7:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 23 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 23 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.7:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamamāravagga "
msgstr "1. About Māra "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn23.7:0.3"
msgid "7. Sotāpannasutta "
msgstr "7. A Stream-Enterer "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.193, sc1
msgctxt "sn23.7:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.7:1.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ rādhaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "When Venerable Rādha was seated to one side, the Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn23.7:1.3"
msgid "“pañcime, rādha, upādānakkhandhā. "
msgstr "“Rādha, there are these five grasping aggregates. "

msgctxt "sn23.7:1.4"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn23.7:1.5"
msgid "Rūpupādānakkhandho … pe … viññāṇupādānakkhandho. "
msgstr "The grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn23.7:1.6"
msgid "Yato kho, rādha, ariyasāvako imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti—"
msgstr "When a noble disciple truly understands these five grasping aggregates’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape, "

msgctxt "sn23.7:1.7"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, rādha, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti. "
msgstr "they’re called a noble disciple who is a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn23.7:1.8"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
